Lizeka Tandwa, News24A photo of Hope Zinde at her memorial service (Karabo Ngoepe, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - The son of former SABC board member, the late Hope Zinde, is expected to appear in the Vereeniging Magistrate&rsquo;s Court on Thursday for allegedly assaulting his father.After his release on R10 000 bail for allegedly killing his mother, Mark Warona Zinde, allegedly assaulted his father Lebohang Mohale Manoto on November 6. He was arrested and sent back to prison.The Sowetan reported on November 16 that Zinde allegedly throttled Manoto in his home in Walkerville. He laid charges against Zinde at the De Deur police station.Zinde is facing a charge of assault with intent to do grievous bodily harm.The 23-year-old was arrested in connection with his mother's murder in June.Zinde, 50, was found dead in the boot of her Range Rover in the garage of her home in the Pecanwood Estate, Hartbeespoort, on Saturday, June 11, after a family friend went looking for her. Drugs and a 10kg weight covered in blood were found in the home, police said at the time.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.